	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>koitsu</b> [ Sun Jun 16, 2013 8:18 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NES vs. <span class="posthilit">SNES</span> screen resolution</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />H-Mode (in modes 5 and 6) will do 512 pixels of resolution horizontally, but <strong>does not</strong> affect sprites/OBJ.  Sprites are still limited to their existing sizes (from 8x8 up to 64x64, depending on what OBJ mode (small/large) you choose).<br /><br />TL;DR -- Stop complaining, work with what you've got.  Spoiled.  :P

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


